    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 211.94/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Governor-General Forbes asks me to cause arrest here and hold for extradition a
                    Filipino charged with murder. The Japanese Government requests me to state,
                    before acting, that the Philippine Islands are to be considered within our
                    extradition treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O’Brien.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
